Repository state handoff - 2026-05-12

Completed slice:
- Added Chumsky 0.13.0-based lexer foundation in `linguini-syntax`.
- Added token/span model and lexer tests for schema fixture, locale fixture, raw text, multiline text, placeholders, comments, doc comments, and byte spans.
- Added spec/checklist rule requiring this `.codex` handoff to be kept current for future LLM continuation.

Implementation decisions:
- Lexer uses `chumsky = "0.13.0"`.
- Public spans are byte offsets.
- Raw text after `=` and `=>` currently includes leading spaces, matching "text after delimiter" literally.
- Mode transitions are coordinated in Rust, while token recognition is done with Chumsky parsers.
- Multiline raw text currently treats `"` as a delimiter boundary so triple quotes can be recognized; escaped/ordinary quotes in raw text are deferred.

Tests last run:
- `cargo test -p linguini-syntax`

Known deferred work:
- Lexer error recovery is not complete.
- Lexer snapshot tests are not added yet.
- Parser implementation has not started.
- Raw text quote handling should be revisited when parser fixtures cover quoted localized text.

Next recommended task:
- Add lexer recovery and snapshot/golden tests, then start the Chumsky parser over the token stream.
